title: Brisbane weather: SEQ unlikely to see more snow
text:
Brisbane weather: SEQ unlikely to see... Brisbane weather: SEQ unlikely to see more snow 3 hrs ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Queensland and New South Wales can expect "a run of chilly days" with a strong cold front sending temperatures plummeting to four degrees in Brisbane. The chances of more snow falling in Queensland during this week's Antarctic Vortex are slim, forecasters say, with a road trip to NSW the best option for snow chasers.   Sydney Morning Herald.
